			<ns0:name>mcgra...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109286297231979736865/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">There are some outstanding issues with the new toolchain_build
infrastructure that are dangerous to future maintainability:

1. Updating TOOL_REVISIONS is a tedious, manual process that is error-prone.
   Managing this file should be mostly automated, so that all a person does
   manually is indicate, &amp;quot;I want to deploy the XYZ toolchain built at NaCl
   revision NNNNN.&amp;quot; and then do the commit.  It seems likely that the best
   way to do this will be to change the form of the file substantially.

2. It's not obvious from looking at the file what the component name_xxxxx
   hashes are about and how they relate (or don't) to the *_HASH values.

3. Nothing (except possibly for comments, which are manual and error-prone)
   associates the component selections with the NaCl revision of
   toolchain_build.py that built them.
